Added: Displaying temperature with tenths. Saving search history with temperature. Button to go to the query history page.
Fixed bug when re-entering a city
caching added
added a button to view the weather in the city the user was looking at earlier
added button showing how many times you have entered what city
Icons and bootstrap styles added
added weather status display, information about the presence of rain or thunderstorms
updated templates where CSS and JavaScript are placed in separate files and pages use template inheritance.
corrected static settings for correct operation of the application via docker
the structure of views and templates has been changed, part of the code has been moved to forms.py
added plugin to get a drop-down list of city names after entering the first letter
minor code changes
implemented Redis to calculate the number of requests by city
added variables for correct operation of Redis
Added error page when entering an invalid city name
integrated Django Rest Framework to manage user search history and provide an API to display search query statistics.
changed access level DEFAULT_PERMISSION_CLASSES from AllowAny
Project structure has been improved. Separation of the code into processing of external APIs and providing data via APIs.
views related to external APIs moved to services.py
Added country flags, parameter icons, wind speed, wind gusts and apparent temperature
Improved tooltips when entering a city name. The Dadata service plugin has been replaced by the GeoName service plugin.
Removed redundancy from the project.
